  "README.md": "# Remark Deflist Revisited ¬∞// Simple Example\n\n[![GH][GH Badge]][GH]\n[![NPM][NPM Badge]][NPM]\n[![JSR][JSR Badge]][JSR]\n[![Downloads][Downloads Badge]][Downloads]\n[![Socket][Socket Badge]][Socket]\n\nMinimalist example of using **`@verikami/remark-deflist-revisited`** in Node.js.\n\n**[Remark Deflist Revisited][module]** is a **[Remark]** plugin. A wrapper around **`remark-deflist`** with improved support for nested definition lists. It preserves all the original functionality and performs additional processing.\n\nSee also examples of **[Express.js]** and **[Cloudflare Worker]** implementations.\n\n## ‚ú® Features\n\n- Pure Node.js with minimal dependencies\n- Exportable functions for reuse\n- File output capability\n- Basic HTML styling\n- Error handling\n\n## üîß Requirements\n\n- Node.js 20 or higher\n- npm or yarn\n\n## üöÄ Quick Start\n\n```bash\n## Install dependencies\n„ÉÑ npm install\n\n## Run server with main example\n„ÉÑ npm start\n\n## Run server with file watching\n„ÉÑ npm run dev\n\n## Run the main generation example\n„ÉÑ npm run gen\n\n## Run with file watching\n„ÉÑ npm run watch\n\n## See example html output\n„ÉÑ npm run example\n\n## Run tests\n„ÉÑ npm test\n```\n\n## üíª Usage Examples\n\n### As a Script\n\n```bash\n„ÉÑ node index.js\n```\n\n### As a Module\n\n```javascript\nimport { processMarkdown, createHTMLPage } from './index.js';\n\nconst html = await processMarkdown('Your **markdown** content');\nconst page = createHTMLPage(html, 'Page Title');\n```\n\n## üìÅ Files\n\n- `index.js` ‚Üí Main processor with exportable functions\n- `example.js` ‚Üí How to use as a module\n- `test.js` ‚Üí Basic functionality tests\n\n## üì¶ Output\n\nRunning `npm start` generates `output.html` file with:\n\n- Processed markdown ‚Üí HTML conversion\n- Definition lists support\n- Basic CSS styling\n\n## üìÑ License\n\nThis project is Open Source and available under the MIT License.\n\n2025 ¬© MIT ¬∞// [veriKami] ¬∞// [Weronika Kami]\n\n[veriKami]: https://verikami.com\n[Weronika Kami]: https://linkedin.com/in/verikami\n\n[module]: https://github.com/veriKami/remark-deflist-revisited\n[Simple]: https://github.com/veriKami/remark-deflist-revisited-simple\n[Express.js]: https://github.com/veriKami/remark-deflist-revisited-express\n[Cloudflare Worker]: https://github.com/veriKami/remark-deflist-revisited-worker\n\n[GH]: https://github.com/veriKami/remark-deflist-revisited\n[GH Badge]: https://img.shields.io/badge/GitHub-Repository-blue?logo=github\n\n[Remark]: https://remark.js.org\n\n[NPM]: https://www.npmjs.com/package/@verikami/remark-deflist-revisited\n[NPM Badge]: https://img.shields.io/npm/v/@verikami/remark-deflist-revisited?logo=npm&logoColor=white&labelColor=red&color=black\n\n[JSR]: https://jsr.io/@verikami/remark-deflist-revisited\n[JSR Badge]: https://jsr.io/badges/@verikami/remark-deflist-revisited\n\n[Downloads]: https://www.npmjs.com/package/@verikami/remark-deflist-revisited\n[Downloads Badge]: https://img.shields.io/npm/dm/@verikami/remark-deflist-revisited.svg\n\n[Socket]: https://socket.dev/npm/package/@verikami/remark-deflist-revisited\n[Socket Badge]: https://badge.socket.dev/npm/package/@verikami/remark-deflist-revisited\n\n",
  "ai/gemini_20250930_debug_nodejs_server.md": "# Podsumowanie Sesji: Debugowanie Podw√≥jnych Log√≥w w Serwerze Node.js\n\n**Data:** 30 wrze≈õnia 2025\n\n## Problem\n\nU≈ºytkowniczka zauwa≈ºy≈Ça, ≈ºe po ka≈ºdym od≈õwie≈ºeniu strony w przeglƒÖdarce, w konsoli serwera Node.js pojawia≈Ç siƒô ten sam komunikat dwa razy. Celem by≈Ço zdiagnozowanie i rozwiƒÖzanie tej anomalii.\n\n## Analiza\n\n1.  **PrzeglƒÖd Kodu:** Rozpoczƒô≈Çam od analizy pliku `server.js`. Okaza≈Ço siƒô, ≈ºe serwer by≈Ç bardzo prosty i nie r√≥≈ºnicowa≈Ç ≈ºƒÖda≈Ñ przychodzƒÖcych na r√≥≈ºne adresy URL.\n\n2.  **Postawienie Hipotezy:** NajczƒôstszƒÖ przyczynƒÖ takiego zachowania jest automatyczne, dodatkowe ≈ºƒÖdanie wysy≈Çane przez przeglƒÖdarkƒô, zazwyczaj w celu pobrania ikony strony (`favicon.ico`). Serwer, nie majƒÖc logiki do obs≈Çugi r√≥≈ºnych ≈õcie≈ºek, traktowa≈Ç to ≈ºƒÖdanie tak samo jak g≈Ç√≥wne ≈ºƒÖdanie o stronƒô, wykonujƒÖc ten sam kod po raz drugi.\n\n3.  **Weryfikacja:** Kod serwera potwierdzi≈Ç tƒô hipotezƒô. Ka≈ºde ≈ºƒÖdanie (niezale≈ºnie od `req.url`) powodowa≈Ço uruchomienie logiki przetwarzania markdownu i logowanie komunikatu do konsoli.\n\n## RozwiƒÖzanie\n\nAby naprawiƒá problem, zmodyfikowa≈Çam logikƒô serwera w pliku `server.js`. Wprowadzi≈Çam warunek, kt√≥ry sprawdza `req.url`:\n\n-   Je≈õli ≈ºƒÖdanie jest skierowane na g≈Ç√≥wnƒÖ ≈õcie≈ºkƒô (`/`), serwer przetwarza markdown i zwraca pe≈ÇnƒÖ stronƒô HTML.\n-   Dla ka≈ºdego innego adresu URL (w tym `/favicon.ico`), serwer zwraca odpowied≈∫ `404 Not Found` i nie wykonuje g≈Ç√≥wnej logiki.\n\nPoni≈ºej znajduje siƒô fragment kodu (`diff`) obrazujƒÖcy wprowadzonƒÖ zmianƒô:\n\n```diff\n-const server = createServer(async (req, res) => {\n-  try {\n-    console.log(\"üëÑ Processing markdown\");\n-\n-    const content = await processMarkdown(markdown);\n-    const page = createHTMLPage(content, \"Simple Markdown Processor\");\n-    // console.log(\"‚úÖ HTML generated successfully\");\n-\n-    res.writeHead(200, { \"Content-Type\": \"text/html\" });\n-    res.end(page);\n-  }\n-  catch (err) {\n-    res.writeHead(500, { 'Content-Type': 'text/plain' });\n-    res.end('Server Error');\n-  }\n-});\n+const server = createServer(async (req, res) => {\n+  if (req.url === \"/\") {\n+    try {\n+      console.log(\"üëÑ Processing markdown for /\");\n+\n+      const content = await processMarkdown(markdown);\n+      const page = createHTMLPage(content, \"Simple Markdown Processor\");\n+\n+      res.writeHead(200, { \"Content-Type\": \"text/html\" });\n+      res.end(page);\n+    } catch (err) {\n+      res.writeHead(500, { \"Content-Type\": \"text/plain\" });\n+      res.end(\"Server Error\");\n+    }\n+  } else {\n+    //: Handle other requests like favicon.ico\n+    //: -----------------------------------------\n+    console.log(`‚ùì Ignoring request for ${req.url}`);\n+    res.writeHead(404, { \"Content-Type\": \"text/plain\" });\n+    res.end(\"Not Found\");\n+  }\n+});\n```\n\n## Weryfikacja\n\nPo wprowadzeniu zmian, u≈ºytkowniczka samodzielnie uruchomi≈Ça serwer i potwierdzi≈Ça, ≈ºe problem zosta≈Ç rozwiƒÖzany. W konsoli pojawia siƒô teraz pojedynczy log dla strony g≈Ç√≥wnej oraz informacja o ignorowaniu ≈ºƒÖdania o `favicon.ico`, zgodnie z oczekiwaniami.\n",
